---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How We Select Products and Guide Topics"
  description="How Australian Home Collective chooses product types, guide topics and everyday home details to cover."
>
  <header class="page-intro">
    <div class="narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">How we choose what to include</p>
      <h1>How We Select Products and Guide Topics</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Our guides are built around practical home decisions first.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>
  <section class="content narrow">
    <p>
      We look at how a product type may fit into everyday Australian homes, including space,
      storage, cleaning, comfort, durability, setup and maintenance.
    </p>

    <h2>What we consider</h2>
    <ul class="feature-list">
      <li>Practical use in everyday homes.</li>
      <li>Room size and storage limits.</li>
      <li>Cleaning and maintenance.</li>
      <li>Materials and durability.</li>
      <li>Safety and suitability.</li>
      <li>Australian availability where relevant.</li>
      <li>Clear product information from retailers or brands.</li>
      <li>Whether the item solves a real household problem.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we handle product claims</h2>
    <p>
      We avoid making claims that cannot be reasonably supported. If a guide discusses a
      product type, feature or home setup detail, the wording should make clear whether it is
      general guidance, public product information or hands-on experience.
    </p>

    <h2>Hands-on testing</h2>
    <p>
      We do not claim hands-on testing unless it has actually happened and is clearly stated.
      Most guides are practical buying guides designed to help readers compare product types
      and features before choosing what suits their home.
    </p>

    <h2>Prices and availability</h2>
    <p>
      Prices, availability, shipping terms and retailer details can change. Readers should
      check the retailer's current product page before buying.
    </p>

    <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
    <p>
      Some pages may contain affiliate links. This does not change the aim of the guide:
      practical, useful home guidance first. You can read the full <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
